HOW DO RADIOATIVE NEUCLEI BECOME UNSTABLE--------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Which atoms are unstable?

1. All elements with atomic numbers greater than 83
2. Nuclei outside the "Belt of stability" (uneven proton:neutron ratio).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

4 types of radiation

1. Alpha particles are helium nuclei. Low Penetrating Power.
2. Beta particles are like speedy electrons. Medium Penetrating power.
3. Gamma rays are high energy rays. High penetrating power
4. Positron are like postive beta rays. medium penetrating power.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

